    "HomeKit Scene Triggers (Settings → Tools → Scene Trigger) automatically run a HomeKit scene when your network health grade drops to or below a chosen threshold. Use this to, for example, turn on a smart lamp in the room with the failing device." : {
      "comment" : "User Manual paragraph describing the HomeKit scene trigger feature.",
      "extractionState" : "stale",
      "localizations" : {
        "sv" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "HomeKit-scenutlösare (Inställningar → Verktyg → Scenutlösare) kör automatiskt en HomeKit-scen när ditt nätverkshälsobetyg sjunker till eller under ett valt tröskelvärde. Använd detta för att till exempel tända en smart lampa i rummet med den felande enheten."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Hop count = routing steps from border router. Each additional hop adds latency. Aim for 3 hops or fewer." : {
      "comment" : "A description of the hop count, which indicates the number of routing steps from the border router.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true,
      "localizations" : {
        "sv" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
